abstract: Tight end Randy McMichael did not sound impressed with the Jets after San Diego's 27-21 loss.
snippet: Tight end Randy McMichael did not sound impressed with the Jets after San Diego's 27-21 loss.
lead_paragraph: EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. - The verbal jousting that accompanied the Jets' game Sunday did not end at kickoff. It continued after their 27-21 victory, in the Chargers' locker room, where tight end Randy McMichael sounded rather unimpressed with the Jets' defense.

headline.main: One Charger Doesn't Go Down Quietly
